						"title": "The blueprint to coffee shop networking",
						"subtitle": null,
						"copy": "Working from a cafe is simple: grab a coffee, open your laptop, and connect. Modern enterprises are now bringing that same simplicity to branches, stores, and remote sites with a \"coffee shop networking\" approach. This model offers consistent, secure connectivity without the complexity of legacy \"hub-and-spoke\" networks.\n\nThis whitepaper explains how to transition to this light-branch, heavy-cloud architecture with a secure access service edge (SASE) platform. \n\nDownload this guide to learn how to minimize your on-premises hardware, deliver consistent user experiences, and enforce zero trust security across three key steps:\n\n- __Step 1: Modernize user-to-app access__ and replace legacy VPNs with faster, safer zero trust network access (ZTNA)\n- __Step 2: Simplify branch connectivity__ and reduce reliance on bulky on-prem hardware and expensive MPLS lines\n- __Step 3: Secure web and cloud access__ to block web threats and gain shadow AI/IT visibility without performance trade-offs\n\n![BDES-8941 CSN Hero Illustration Connectivity 03](//cf-assets.www.cloudflare.com/slt3lc6tev37/3ED2JN5iB3EKJ28N3d022j/d177a2acb5ce576c59592b424a407e94/BDES-8941_CSN_Hero_Illustration_Connectivity_03.png)",
